1.2.0 (Feb 8th, 2026)
Added more ways of adding packages
=> GitHub
=> GitLab
=> CodeBerg
=> zeP (via the main packages [fallback to old way])
=> Local
Help message improved
Fixed naming schemes
Reduced LoC (de-dup)
Coding scheme improvement

1.1.0 (Jan 26th, 2026)
Moved the root folder to ~/.zep instead (added migrate function)
Removed artifact pruning, uninstall does it by default after each uninstallation
API Route changes
On Installation, setup is not run by default
Setup does not print information out or requests to be run, if required
Migration runs by default on each run
zep and zig executeables are located at ~/.zep/bin now.
Docs have been moved around and seperated
Installation bug fixes => "Extracting..." hung.
zep.json is now obsolete
Installation fixes corrupt files [smart install]
bufPrint => allocPrint (more predictable)
.zep/.conf/injector.json is now obsolete
zep.lock stores all required data.
When creating a new package, most data is taken from the .lock file instead of being prompted.
Responses for y/N answers; "Ok.".
Removed clap.zig from dependecies, as it was giving more trouble than needed.
Verbosity can be specified
During Installation progress is displayed [zig/zep installations]
Added Cache control for artifacts (Zig/Zep)
Printing Changes
Command name changes (added aliases aswell)

